message: "If you use KinshipQA in your work, please cite the paper below."
title: "KinshipQA: A Multi-Hop Kinship Reasoning Benchmark Across Anthropological Kinship Systems"
authors:
  - family-names: "[Anonymous]"
    given-names: "[Anonymous]"
version: 6.0.0
date-released: 2026-05-31
repository-code: "https://github.com/[anonymous]/Kinship-Data-Benchmark-for-Multi-hop-Reasoning"
license: MIT
abstract: >
  KinshipQA is a multi-hop kinship reasoning benchmark spanning seven
  anthropological kinship systems (Eskimo, Sudanese, Hawaiian, Iroquois,
  Dravidian, Crow, Omaha). Questions are procedurally generated from
  RDF/OWL family-tree ontologies, with controlled difficulty along
  category, hop count, and kinship system axes. The benchmark evaluates
  whether LLMs can apply cultural kin-naming rules rather than defaulting
  to English biological terms.
